CS 4518 Mobile and Ubiquitous Computing
PA4 Ski Tracker App
Goal: This app allows a user to log on, see the current weather where they are, and start and stop a ski run.

Names: Chloe Polit and Jess Keene

Software sensor:
- Current weather updates from API to let user know current temperature and conditions on the mountains for user display
Hardware sensors:
- Location services for altitude/GPS
- Accelerometer to track speeds of run and if user is stationary
- GPS: Provides continuous coordinate updates every 3 seconds to track run location and detect displacement.

Background Task:
A ForegroundService (ForegroundLocationService run in AndroidManifest and GeofenceTransitionsReciever) continues GPS tracking
even when the app is not being used, making sure run data is not lost.


Instructions:
Run on emulator in Android Studio
Click start run button to begin tracking a run, button appearance should change and click end run button to end run
Refer to the tabs for any further explanation or instruction.
Navigate through bottom bar for pages, go to settings to toggle light/dark mode, change units, and enable background tracking

Resources/References:
GompeiFountainJumpApp and CityExplorerApp for proper implementation of multiple tabs/screens,
MVVM architecture, and utilization of buttons for our main functionality within the app.
The usage of the models package from CityExplorerApp was implemented within our own app.
Also referred to Lecture 17 for further explanation about multiple tabs.

StackOverFlow was referenced for any specific questions we had such as formatting, proper utilization of intent,
and properly displaying a versatile theme/background.